currentDoc: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

currentSuggestions.original: The next day, you woke up and the bee was back on your shoulder, this time shot through with a dart.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The next day, you woke up and the bee was back on your shoulder, this time shot through with a dart.

currentSuggestions.original: You walk away, wondering if you told the truth.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: You walk away, wondering if you told the truth.

currentSuggestions.original: "What a weirdo" you say out loud.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: "What a weirdo" you say out loud.

currentSuggestions.original: He had heard of these rumors, but he thought it was just a bunch of nonsense.

currentSuggestions.original: The next day, they were all dead.
